<body>
<h1>Highway 38 Solutions - Problem Snapshot</h1>
<p class="meta"><b>Sample ID:</b> H38-T001<br><b>Package:</b> Problem Snapshot<br><b>Scenario:</b> Blocked garage bay to first clear move<br><b>Status:</b> Hypothetical customer-ready sample</p>
<div class="visual"><img src="../assets/sample-garage-proof.svg" alt="Garage before and after sample visual"></div>
<h2>Customer input received</h2>
<ul><li>14 phone photos of a cluttered garage bay.</li><li>One note: "Nothing fits and I want to park one vehicle again."</li><li>Known rough dimensions: 28 ft by 40 ft garage, two overhead doors on the short wall.</li><li>No confirmed ceiling height, wall outlet locations, or exact shelving dimensions.</li></ul>
<h2>What Highway 38 sorted</h2>
<table><colgroup><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:25%"><col style="width:25%"></colgroup><tr><th>Visible fact</th><th>Assumption</th><th>Risk</th><th>Missing info</th></tr><tr><td>Vehicle lane is blocked by mixed storage and tools.</td><td>Customer wants parking back before a full remodel.</td><td>Buying cabinets before measuring could waste money.</td><td>Wall length, ceiling height, outlets, door swing, vehicle width.</td></tr><tr><td>Items are mixed: daily tools, seasonal storage, loose parts.</td><td>Some items can be removed or moved high.</td><td>Floor storage will return if there is no assigned zone.</td><td>Which tools are daily-use and which are rarely used.</td></tr></table>
<h2>Customer-ready recommendation</h2>
<div class="note"><b>First clear move:</b> Do not buy cabinets yet. Clear one vehicle lane, measure the long wall and ceiling height, then choose either wall rail storage or shelving as the first storage purchase.</div>
<h2>First five actions</h2>
<ol><li>Mark a 10 ft wide vehicle lane with tape or chalk.</li><li>Move anything in that lane to a temporary sort zone.</li><li>Measure wall length, ceiling height, outlet locations, and overhead door clearance.</li><li>Sort items into daily tools, seasonal storage, parts, trash, and unknown.</li><li>Choose first storage spend only after the wall/ceiling measurement is confirmed.</li></ol>
<h2>QA handoff</h2>
<table><colgroup><col style="width:32%"><col style="width:68%"></colgroup><tr><th>Check</th><th>Pass standard</th></tr><tr><td>Goal restated</td><td>Customer wants one vehicle bay back.</td></tr><tr><td>Assumptions separated</td><td>Assumptions are not mixed with facts.</td></tr><tr><td>Next action clear</td><td>Clear lane and measure before buying.</td></tr><tr><td>Boundary visible</td><td>This is practical planning, not engineering, permit, electrical, or code signoff.</td></tr></table>
<p class="small">Highway 38 Solutions - Big problems. Clear plans. This is a hypothetical sample deliverable.</p>
</body>
</html>
